9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 638, L.D. 978, “An Act to Increase
10 General Assistance Reimbursement for Municipalities and Indian Tribes”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §4308, sub-§1-A, as enacted by PL 2011, c. 655, Pt. R, §2, is
14 amended to read:
15 1-A. Limit on housing assistance. Except as provided in subsections 1‑B and 2,
16 housing assistance provided pursuant to this chapter is limited to a maximum of 9 months
17 during the period from July 1, 2012 to June 30, 2013. Beginning July 1, 2025, except as
18 provided in subsections 1‑B and 2, housing assistance provided pursuant to this chapter is
19 limited to a maximum of 12 months in a 36-month period.
20 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §4308, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2023, c. 643, Pt. II, §1, is
21 further amended by amending the 2nd blocked paragraph to read:
22 A municipality may not exceed maximum levels of assistance established pursuant to
23 section 4305 for an applicant household for more than 30 days in a 12-month period when
24 assistance is granted for housing in a hotel, motel, inn or other lodging place as defined in
25 section 2491, subsection 7‑F.
26 Sec. 3. 22 MRSA §4311, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2015, c. 267, Pt. SSSS, §1, is
27 further amended to read:
28 1. Departmental reimbursement. When a municipality incurs net general assistance
29 costs in any fiscal year prior to July 1, 2015 in excess of .0003 of that municipality's most
30 recent state valuation relative to the state fiscal year for which reimbursement is being
31 issued, as determined by the State Tax Assessor in the statement filed as provided in Title
32 36, section 381, the Department of Health and Human Services shall reimburse the
33 municipality for 90% of the amount in excess of these expenditures when the department
34 finds that the municipality has been in compliance with all requirements of this chapter. If
35 a municipality elects to determine need without consideration of funds distributed from any
