5 The department shall reimburse each municipality and each Indian tribe 70% of the direct
6 costs incurred by that municipality or tribe on or after July 1, 2015 and before July 1, 2025
7 for the general assistance program granted by that municipality or tribe. For the purposes
8 of this subsection, "Indian tribe" has the same meaning as in section 411, subsection 8‑A.
9 The department shall reimburse each municipality and Indian tribe as follows:
10 A. Beginning July 1, 2025, the department shall reimburse each municipality and each
11 Indian tribe 75% of the direct costs incurred by that municipality or tribe for costs
12 incurred on or after July 1, 2025 and before July 1, 2027; and
13 B. Beginning July 1, 2027, the department shall reimburse each municipality and each
14 Indian tribe 80% of the direct costs incurred by that municipality or tribe for costs
15 incurred on or after July 1, 2027.
16 For the purposes of this subsection, "Indian tribe" has the same meaning as in section 411,
17 subsection 8-A.
18 Sec. 4. 22 MRSA §4323, sub-§6, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 575, §6, is repealed.
19 Sec. 5. 22 MRSA §4327, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 575, §7, is amended to read:
20 §4327. Reporting
21 The department shall use municipal reports, data from the statewide online database
22 required under section 4323, subsection 6 and other metrics to generate a general assistance
23 report to be submitted to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
24 over general assistance matters no later than January 30, 2026 and no later than January
25 30th of each odd-numbered calendar year thereafter. The initial report must include
26 recommendations regarding a potential extension of the general assistance eligibility period
27 beyond the 30-day limit established in section 4310, subsection 4. All reports must include
28 metrics for: the number of individuals and families who received funds; the basic
29 necessities for which those funds were provided; the length of time those funds were
30 received; which municipalities accessed technical assistance and the number of times that
31 technical assistance was requested, including instances outside of normal business hours;
32 the type of technical assistance municipalities required; the number of calls to the
33 department's general assistance hotline; and the number and content of complaints received
34 and additional metrics as determined necessary by the department. The report must also
35 include data illustrating municipal poverty levels, or regional or county poverty data when
36 municipal-level poverty data is unavailable, and data regarding the use of other public
37 benefit programs such as the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program and the
38 Temporary Assistance for Needy Families program in each municipality.
39 Sec. 6. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
40 allocations are made.
